Dignitaries, including former President Jacob Zuma, have arrived at the Royal house in KwaNongoma KZN. They are paying their respects to the late AmaZulu King Goodwill Zwelithini. Due to COVID-19 protocols, the Royal house has decided the remains of the king will not lie in state at the Royal Palace. Senior reporter Siphamandla Goge reports. #DStv403​. JOHANNESBURG - The late King Goodwill Zwelithini will be buried at night and by men only. That's the word from AmaZulu Prime Minister, Prince Mangosuthu Buthulezi. A number of dignitaries have arrived at KwaNongoma to pay their last respects. A memorial service will be held for the late monarch on Thursday. The AmaZulu Royal Family had earlier confirmed King Goodwill Zwelithini will be laid to rest on Thursday. READ: Royal Family decides King Goodwill Zwelithini will not lie in state The king's body arrived at the royal palace on Saturday. King Zwelithini passed away on Friday morning after a long battle with diabetes. President Cyril Ramaphosa has accorded him a special official funeral, category 1.